  <ability>
    <abilitytitle>Politics</abilitytitle>
    <abilityid>lore.politics</abilityid>
    <abilityclass>Non-Combat</abilityclass>
    <abilityattrmodifiers></abilityattrmodifiers>
    <abilitydescription>
      <p>
	This ability represents the study of the machinations that occur in the
	upper levels of power in society, its application, its history and its heraldry.
	This includes political theory: Real Politics and Machiavellian dealings
	and important historical treaties and maneveurings.
      </p>
    </abilitydescription>    
    <abilitylevels>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>1</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>6</defaultlore>
        <defaultmartial>0</defaultmartial>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>2</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 vs DDC 12</check>	
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    The character has knowledge of the history and current affairs of some
	    local regions nobility and royalty.  They know the heraldic insignias
	    of these nobles and important state organizations.  They understand
	    the laws of succession in that region.  They know most of the
	    commonly known court intrigue.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
      </abilitylevel>

      <abilitylevel>
        <levelnumber>2</levelnumber>
        <defaultlore>6</defaultlore>
        <defaultgeneral>0</defaultgeneral>
        <successes>2</successes>
        <attempts>2</attempts>
        <check>Std 2d8 + 2 vs DDC 12</check>	
	<leveldescription>
	  <p>
	    The character has 1st level knowledge of two other regions and has deep
	    knowledge of their own region.  They may know some tightly kept secrets.
	  </p>
	</leveldescription>
        <prereqabilitylevel>school.scholar_1</prereqabilitylevel>	
      </abilitylevel>
    </abilitylevels>
  </ability>


